4. Ways to Declare Variables

Answer =>
There are three main ways to declare variables in JavaScript:

a) var – Old way, function-scoped. Can be redeclared and updated.
    <!-- var name = "Alice";
    name = "Bob"; // update
    var name = "Charlie"; // redeclare -->

b) let – Modern, block-scoped. Can be updated, but cannot be redeclared in the same block.
    <!-- let age = 25;
    age = 26; // update -->

c) const – Constant, block-scoped. Cannot be reassigned.
    <!-- const pi = 3.1416;
    pi = 3.14; // ❌ Error -->